com.parrot.arsdk.arcommands

Class ARCommand

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.parrot.arsdk.arsal.ARNativeData
      • com.parrot.arsdk.arcommands.ARCommand

  • public class ARCommand
extends ARNativeData
    Java representation of a C ARCommand object.
    This class holds either app-generated objects, that are to be sent to the device, or network-generated objects, that are to be decoded by the application.

    • Field Summary

        Class Piloting description:
        All commands related to piloting the totoDrone

        Command MoveBy description:
        Draft: this command is not implemented yet by the firmware
        Move the drone to a relative position and rotate heading by a given angle
        The frame is horizontal and relative to the current drone orientation:
        - X is front
        - Y is right
        - Z is down
        The movement settings of the device are those set for the autonomous flight.

        _dX - Wanted displacement along the front axis [m]
        _dY - Wanted displacement along the right axis [m]
        _dZ - Wanted displacement along the down axis [m]
        _dPsi - Wanted rotation of heading [rad]
        Returns:
        An ARCOMMANDS_GENERATOR_ERROR_ENUM error code.

        public ARCOMMANDS_GENERATOR_ERROR_ENUM setSkyControllerCalibrationEnableMagnetoCalibrationQualityUpdates(byte enable)
        Set an ARCommand to hold the command EnableMagnetoCalibrationQualityUpdates of class Calibration in project SkyController

        Project SkyController description:
        All SkyController-only commands

        Class Calibration description:
        Commands related to the SkyController sensors calibration

        Command EnableMagnetoCalibrationQualityUpdates description:
        Asks the SkyController to send (or not) the magneto calibration quality updates.
        The MagnetoCalibrationState will always be sent when the status parameters changes,
        regardless of this setting.

        This function reuses the current ARCommand, replacing its content with a new command created from the current params
        Parameters:
        _enable - Flag to enable the feature.
        _enable - 1 = enable quality updates
        _enable - 0 = disable quality updates
        Returns:
        An ARCOMMANDS_GENERATOR_ERROR_ENUM error code.

      • setSkyControllerCalibrationStateMagnetoCalibrationState

        public ARCOMMANDS_GENERATOR_ERROR_ENUM setSkyControllerCalibrationStateMagnetoCalibrationState(ARCOMMANDS_SKYCONTROLLER_CALIBRATIONSTATE_MAGNETOCALIBRATIONSTATE_STATUS_ENUM status,
                                                                                               byte X_Quality,
                                                                                               byte Y_Quality,
                                                                                               byte Z_Quality)
        Set an ARCommand to hold the command MagnetoCalibrationState of class CalibrationState in project SkyController

        Project SkyController description:
        All SkyController-only commands

        Class CalibrationState description:
        State of the SkyController calibration

        Command MagnetoCalibrationState description:
        The current state of the magnetometer calibration

        This function reuses the current ARCommand, replacing its content with a new command created from the current params
        Parameters:
        _status - The global status of the calibration
        _X_Quality - Calibration quality on X axis.
        _X_Quality - 0 is bad, 255 is perfect
        _Y_Quality - Calibration quality on Y axis.
        _Y_Quality - 0 is bad, 255 is perfect
        _Z_Quality - Calibration quality on Z axis.
        _Z_Quality - 0 is bad, 255 is perfect
        Returns:
        An ARCOMMANDS_GENERATOR_ERROR_ENUM error code.
